<title>COLOMBIA: Swedish bank makes Colombian power plant loan.</title>
<headline>Swedish bank makes Colombian power plant loan.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Colombia will sign a $58 million loan deal with Sweden's Nordbanken in order to complete one of the country's largest hydroelectric projects in northwest Cordoba province, officials said Wednesday.</p>
<p>The state-run Empresa Multiproposito Urra 1, which is building the 340 megawatt Urra 1 hydroelectric generating plant on the Sinu River, will pay back the loan over 14 years, including a five-year grace period, at 7.5 percent interest, the company's executive director Alfredo Solano told Reuters.</p>
<p>Solano said he hoped to sign for the loan within the next 15 days and that the funds would be used to offset the $197 million needed to complete the project which has an estimated total cost of $723 million.</p>
<p>Solano said he was looking to raise the remaining $140 million from foreign and national banks. The project's target completion date is 1999, he said.</p>
<p>((-- Javier Mozzo, Bogota newsroom, 571 610 7944))</p>
